
[1]emporium

   EMPO'RIUM, n. [L. from the Gr. to buy; to pass or go.]

   1. A place of merchandize; a town or city of trade; particularly, a
   city or town of extensive commerce, or in which the commerce of an
   extensive country centers, or to which sellers and buyers resort from
   different countries. Such are London, Amsterdam and Hamburg. New York
   will be an emporium.

   2. in medicine, the common sensory in the brain.
